<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>POLITICS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/06/politics/06COND.html?todaysheadlines">Condit Loses House Race to Former Aide</a></b><br>
Representative Gary A. Condit lost the Democratic primary for his seat to Assemblyman Dennis Cardoza on Tuesday night.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/06/politics/06DONA.html?todaysheadlines">Delay Tactics Set the Stage for a Showdown on Campaign Financing Bill</a></b><br>
A Senate confrontation over changing the   campaign finance law now appears likely after one Republican blocked the measure from coming to   a swift vote.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/06/business/06STEE.html?todaysheadlines">Bush Puts Tariffs of as Much as 30% on Steel Imports</a></b><br>
Taking broad federal action, President Bush imposed tariffs on most types of steel imported into the United States from Europe, Asia and South America.
<P>
</font>













<p>
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/pages/politics/index.html?todaysheadline">MORE POLITICS NEWS</a>
