<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>SPORTS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/06/sports/basketball/06NETS.html?todaysheadlines">Lakers Hold Off the Nets</a></b><br>
The Nets stormed back to take a lead in the fourth quarter but were unable to hold on in a loss to the Los Angeles Lakers.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/06/sports/ncaabasketball/06EAST.html?todaysheadlines">In Upended Big East, First Round Matters Most</a></b><br>
It used to be that Friday night was the must-attend session of the Big East tournament. Now, it is the   first-round games on Wednesday.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/06/sports/baseball/06SOXX.html?todaysheadlines">Red Sox Fire Manager</a></b><br>
Boston Red Sox Manager Joe Kerrigan was fired by the team's new owners and replaced on an interim basis by the third-base coach, Mike Cubbage.
<P>
</font>













<p>
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/pages/sports/index.html?todaysheadline">MORE SPORTS NEWS</a>
<br>

